It like really sucks, until you do it, then it's actually kind of cool.  I'll give it hard, because 9/10 times it's really hard. Then you catch it on the right day. Then it's soft. The real prize is never having to touch it again.

Fun figuring out the Beta with Shirley on this one.  Went smoothly after I decided to stop punting from the top, but taking some slams is nice sometimes, even if you miss the pads... Shirley thinks he's being a noble hardman calling this soft, but really he just doesn't realize how strong he is... P.S. Shoutout SB South. They'd probably be pretty psyched on looking at this thing, even though it's too tall for them to ever pull on.

Still a fun problem from the natural stand, with the lower start adding some hard cool moves. Next time for the low. Assuming I'm willing to tackle Hell's Half Mile again...gotta retrieve that chalk bag I guess
Kinda fun little rig.  Might have another name somewhere...would be interesting to see the new outlying areas book, but not 50 dollars interesting. More people should come up here.

Pulled this quick before heading up to see Fanny crush The Swarm like a boss (shout-out). Decently cool movement. Woulda DG'd the PG but you made the mistake of taunting me Shirley. I saw Konkey's texts!

Crazy surprise send, couple years later and maybe I've gotten a touch better at rock climbing? Sweet power endurance test piece, popped 8 pulleys and ripped both nipples clean off body dragging up this clean, aesthetic line.

Soft Second GO

I was pretty cranky when I began to bleed through my raw little sausage fingers pulling onto the first hold of the weekend. Thankfully for everyone else, I continued to climb through my tantrum, topped out, and giggled like a little school girl all the way down. Maybe someday I will actually grow some skin. Or get a Johns Hopkins hand. First jump is pretty damn hard for me. Soft
Forgot about this thing. A Scotty B special! Tricky and a bit heady, good to get on when Crossroads is taking a big dump all over you.

Finally made it up here with only a mild injury instead of a heinous one and pulled out the m-flash through some strange magic. Considering all bouldering is inherently stupid, this is really good! 9/10 Would bang again! Shout-out Dustin!

Awesome! I'm always impressed when I encounter something like this while practicing on boulders for real climbing.  And, maybe, with enough practice, I just might become as superlative at topping out as Chase! At least on practice problems. I'll still chuff the 5.8 mantles on all my real-climbing projects.

This thing is pretty cool in that it is the obvious straight-up line as compared to High Plains. But god damn did it feel hard. Felt harder than the latter for me, but maybe it's a tall person thing. Was planning on going left hand to the last sloper, but when I got up there on the send go I had a change of heart and went right. *snicker snicker* >;)

Some of the most fun I've had bouldering. The crimps felt a lot better 2 years later. Never knew in the past how I was gonna tackle the last few moves, ended up going with the screaming banshee right hand dyno to the lip, skipping the last intemediate crimp. Turns out I should jump more often, because it worked the first time I tried it. Can M-SoftSecondGO be a thing? So lesson here kids is that even in the face of a glaring lack of natural ability or strength, even a human piece of shit can climb soft V8 (but probably not 9). Just gotta scream a little bit.  Shout-out longest log ever. And Chase and Davey for epic train.

And so the Go Granny trifecta is completed. Kind of sad now that it's all over...no more perfectly mediocre drop offs left... Can't really give it the Soft Second GO as I've been on the other two variants, but that being said, Soft Second GO
I can feel it getting bigger in my hand!

Bouldering is of course really stupid, but sometimes you find a boulder like this that is an exception to the rule, and proves that bouldering can be immensely stupid. Almost as easy as Low Tide, so probably warrants an Australian 22.

I REMEMBER YOU WAS CONFLICTED
Ugh gotta finish these Joe's logs. Tedium ensues

Really stoked Nalle got to watch me chuff off the first move. Didn't feel too hard except for dry firing off of every hold. I'm also super wet for Nalle Huckatallwall, so it was cool having him there.  Obviously I didn't acknowledge him though. I said "Hey man how's it going" and pretended I didn't know who he was so I would seem like a cool soul climber who doesn't tune-in to the media hype train. Then I proceeded to climb like an idiot. But big bonus, I climbed The Angler way smoother than Daila Ojeda, so I could probably be eskimo brothers with Sharma. He is from Santa Cruz...

Nothing like being frozen solid in a total blizzard on the only rest day of trip. Ate shit in my nikes on this one. Tasted good. I'll finish these logs eventually.

That was quite an emotional roller coaster. Ryan was a sweepy wittle cwanky baby today, in part due to being kept up all night by that damn WalMart tent. The winds were a-howlin, and the tent was a-screamin. For 8 hours. Anyways, after giving one burn apiece to each of the TP's on this boulder and not M-fraishing, I decided I needed to walk as far away as possible, splay out face down on a rock, and drift off in a stew of self-pity for an hour or so. When I awoke, I unfortunately had not been carried away to a distant fantasy world in which I could be the instrument of my own agency, but on the upside, I believe enough time had passed at a sufficiently distant proximity to the boulder for my M-fraish gauge to reset. So I did that. In terms of difficulty I'd probably say this > Saigon V6 > Tour de France V6, so 7 is probably good.

Time to finish these Joe's logs I guess... I mean I have an obligation as a rock athlete to keep the world up-to-date on spray. Let's see what do I remember about this...oh yeah I remember Tang being really fucked up for a while until we realized it had broken. Also Kwiddles crushed as per usual. Um, shout-out Mark, I know you're out there.
Shout-out Jquee for crushing this so hard, and getting me psyched enough to follow suit! I didn't even chuff the top! Can u believe?
This was really fucking sketchy
Dang this was hard I think
Ended up putting a few sessions on this despite never really seeking it out. Pretty delicate! Tough for me even though I'm a lanky mofo. So nice down by the river.
Holy soft!
Memory is fuzzy, but this was freaking hard I think. Pulled just in time with the headlamps fading. Also not exactly a dyno iirc? Good times up there with Scott, David, and Daniel!
Burly, crimpy, and aesthetic. Felt much easier this year. But still hard. Such an epic hackey sack sesh after. Wait til you see the vid.
Blech
Super fun, just a tad short. But you're way up above New Joe's so the view is pretty nice. Well that's it, all caught up.
That one guy broke his ass on this remember?

Nobody likes the name with "From" in it? Oh well, guess I'll conform. Joe's highlight! Last day of trip, I had eight completely bloody shit tips covered in tape and glue, I fell from pretty much the top, I almost melted down like a POS, and then I sent! One of my favs!

Happy Earth Week! Free park admission for all! And it will only take you 40 minutes to get from Sentinel to Camp 4! Traffic aside, glad this thing felt pretty cruiser for a change. Tons of fun, nice to feel graceful and precise on a slab for once in a blue  suede moon.

For the first time in months, I didn't start bleeding through a pad (or 3) 10 minutes into a trip. Praise Zeus!  After taking blood-squirting out of the equation, and adding in a solid 2.5 hours worth of sleep the night before, this rig became highly enjoyable! Don't worry though, Squirt Daddy will be back soon enough I'm sure. Shout-out Creed and Mack for spots and laughs!

After blowing out my knee and spending a hot day going for repeats and jestpieces, this was a nice surprise. Fun move reaching up high into an undercling followed by an awkward jump around a bulge off a bad hold to an unreal sick mega god-tier jug. Feel like name is misleading though, pogo doesn't make much sense. Fun day hanging with Creed, Mack, Teddy, and Jolie!

Wow! 2 new problems in one day at CRSP?! Didn't think it was possible. This  bad boy was pretty tricky and pretty sicky. Techy barndoor arete and then, if you're a wanker (and I am), jump! Also let loose a bunch of drool as you top out for good measure.

When the rain beats down and the heat swelters elsewhere, one must go to CRSP. But lo and behold! I actually finished something here.  Seeing Scotty B on the side of the road as I drove up really brightened my day. So, uh, shout-out Scott. I finally hit you back on Venmo the other day. Also shout-out Connor because he requested it. And of course shout-out Mack, way to be a good sport about getting decked. Who knows, maybe I'll become a castle troll yet?
Sharpness and hardness made for a fairly ugly flash. Could tell it would get better after a couple more goes. Can't think of anything notable, so guess I'll just leave this log vanilla.

Solo mission was a success! Minus the inherent failure of being a lonely loser. After spending the morning in Berkeley flip-flopping, I decided to go for it, and got my ass up here early afternoon with a sweet payload of 2 blown-ass mad pads and a 20+ year old Misty halfer. Without another soul in sight, I spent about 5 minutes warming up on a single burn of O.U.A.T., most of which was spent 2/3rds of the way up shaking vigorously and reevaluating my life choices. With confidence now thoroughly boosted, I proceeded to stuff my backpack with sweaters to add an extra something to the most suspect pad deployment ever. 20 minutes later I was up on the arete, one move away, wishing I hadn't put the pads in all the wrong places, when all of the sudden a vision of the UCLA-front-wall-left-arete came to me and said "cross the left hand". And so it was done. And after a few minutes of solitary elation amongst the trees, I was again reminded of how truly alone I am, and how meaningless boulder problems will never fill the void... PSYCH!! SOFT.
Finally made it out to this Curry stuff, and this was pretty damn fun. Quite a fatty move I must say. Too bad my heel popped on the fraish go. Shout-out to stoney bros bumping electronica.

Fun day being dragged around the old guy trav circuit with JB and Strong  Joe (did I mention he's strong?). Not as hard as I thought with appropriate heel-toe cam usage, although my ankle did pop once 0_o Next step after finishing this fine testpiece is taking Joe up on his offer to mold me into a top-class (5.11a) sport climber. He had a sick joke about swapping recipes.

Guess I should throw this up before I forget. Always very epic going for the north coast day trip from Santa Cruz, but the Bang Bus rallied and went for it, making for a solid day of shenanigans with Swedge, Creedman, Harris, and cArL33. Sure, we touched two boulders, but at least they were good? I wish. This thing is a heaping pile of choss.............just kidding Connor, it's obviously and unquestionably very sick. Too bad we didn't have it in us to grow sweet 25 foot schlongs and jump for da lip on that other thing... Oh well, next day trip for sure!

Chase was pysched on my dope, unnecessary finishing dyno. Did it for the lulz obviously. Leaving at 6 so I can have the softsecondGO, my favorite eydaydotnu feature, hope it makes it into the betadaught8Adotnu
Ouch
Got to climb with Jenny again! YAYYYYYY

Gotta hit that undercling HARD. Like HARD AS FUCK. Can't wait to tell Jeff about this around the watercooler once I'm finished being annoying on 8a.moo  ....Also cool compression, bit of a meandering top.
Dang it, forgot to do the sit. Classic crimps amirite!
harder than Black Matter
Very cool. Thoughtful sequence. Mucho photogenic. Glad I didn't kick Scott in the face! What's on the radio in Texas...?
squirty
Fairly cool line in the north area at Medlicott. No need to dyno. Can't we just give things names? Would probably call this one "Squirt Daddy Strikes Back"
Big fat stinky slab around corner from The Scoop. Too bad I called for a pad 2/3rds up and lost all hard man status.
such slime

If I keep forgetting to log on eightay dot noo I may as well quit climbing right? Better get caught up. Let's see, sand levels made this a bit shorter than usual as far as I could tell. Too short to be onsightable, only flaishable.
Hot everywhere, so we go to the beach, where it is also hot. Dank. Goopy sweat-sand almost popped my shoe off on this one

Compression arete thing to the right of Fragile Term. Don't know if the rumored boulder shift made it so you could start lower, but we started low in the jug slot. Felt a touch harder than V4, but probably because I'm a soft, tired, punk ass bitch

Nice half day out screwing around with Strong Joe, Melissa, and of course JB. Hate to be that guy... but isn't this thing a little bit sharp? And a little bit traversey? Like, a sharp traverse? Oh well, still pretty cool I guess. High feet weirdness made this feel pretty hard I thought. For 6C. And so the never ending journey through fifty shades of V5 continues.
Soft mantle is soft. In approach shoes. Psych, only a douche would say that. .....but I was in my approach shoes. And it was soft. I hate myself. But I hate bees more.

A bit salty because Hotos and Handtools is lame and sucks, but this problem is at least kind of cool. Joe kept his topout scary and exciting, so that was cool. JB couldn't roll the lip because his wrist doesn't bend backwards, but I'll give it to him anyways. Also so many bees god damn. More bees than I ever seen had me like "Oh god not the BEES". Bees are soft.
Meat wasps everywhere

Should rename to S2G Arete. Best boulder in Tuolumne Scott? For real? What about Hit or Miss. Anyways this is pretty good. Watch out for a potentially dirt filled top if nobody has been here in a while.
So many aretes at Kitty. This is good fun. Good height too. Name should be The Guitar Problem. Don't we have enough god damn Rastafarian references in climbing already?

Went real quick once I put my beta together, which was a nice change of pace from andyliu84 videos and heinous sprayers like Chase, Scott and Jacquie (jk guys luv ya ;) ) A bit unfortunate that it cuts so far left at the top. Was checking out the potential for the straight up finish. Looked like a super scary, super rounded desperate grovel over. But probably not scarier than the supposed run and jumps. Someone do it.
Technically I did this part first hehehe...
Techy. Aretes are fun when I'm not slipping all over them like an idiot. Big props to JB for taking it down and scoring the 30 years later repeat.
Classico. Tall. Arete. Shout-out JB for making me a scared spotter.
Yuck. To the right of Kitty Arete. Top kinda redeems it.

At the end of a day of repeats sparsely peppered in amongst socializing at the Buttermilk Country Club, it was nice to get on this thing to discover that even though it is now soft, contrary to my earlier memories, it does, indeed, still suck. Plz add M-Flash to dropdown.
That was confusingly hard. I can finally climb V2. Thanks Davey for the beer.

My apologies to everyone camping that heard the screams around 7:30 Friday night. And shout-out to Fanny for repeatedly reminding me to push throughout the ~2 minutes I was up top in the pitch black darkness without a working headlamp. Almost styled it, but you know, not everyone can be beautiful. And some people will never be beautiful. Like me. Felt more like wrestling a 600 pound hog than doing a boulder, and I continued to hyperventilate until we finally settled in at Las Palmas 45 minutes later. But alas, the saga comes to an end, and the V6 Master List is nearly complete! SOFT

Kind of randomly ended up on this, only to discover that it's really pretty good. Not as hard nor as scary as it looks. Nice that there's still a real quality line on this face after the breakage on Suspended. Sweet send train with the #sweetboys

Finally, the epic is complete. One good from the finish punt in true "People's Champion" style followed by a rarely experienced moment of lightness. Came full circle on this, and after a lot of whining, I guess I'll admit it' pretty good. Not pretty, but fun climbing. I mean, not fun enough for my #sweetboy Chase. understandably.
